 Search... News Archive Vacancies Price list About Research Collection Ordering cultures Publications Database Service Courses Meetings Links Workshop on clinical Fusarium in Coimbatore, India! On the 9th of January 2014, an international workshop on clinical Fusarium and fusariosis was held in Coimbatore, India in conjunction with the SIHAM2014 conference of the Indian Society for Human and Animal Mycology. The workshop was organized by the Dept of Microbiology, PSG, and Aravind Eye Hospital in Coimbatore, the LV Prasad Eye Institute in Hyderabad and the CBS-KNAW Fungal Biodiversity Centre, with support from the international society for Human and Animal Mycology (ISHAM). Increase of prices for cultures and services of CBS Due to ever-increasing preservation, operational and maintenance costs, the CBS unfortunately has to increase its prices of cultures and services for the first time since our last increase in 2009. New edition of popular fungal biodiversity calendar: Battle of the pixels continues! In April 2013 the CBS-KNAW Fungal Biodiversity Centre launched its new (12 month) fungal calendar series, focusing on the beauty of fungal biodiversity. KNVvM jaarlijkse meeting van de Sectie Mycologie Op vrijdag 29 november 2013 werd de jaarlijkse meeting van de sectie Mycologie van de KNVvM gehouden op het CBS/Hubrecht complex. De dag bestond uit een aantal lezingen van experts uit binnen- en buitenland en ook uit een zestal voordrachten van Ph.D studenten en postdocs. Address Visiting address: Uppsalalaan 8 3584 CT Utrecht the Netherlands Postal address: P.O. Box 85167 3508 AD Utrecht the Netherlands Tel + 31 (0)30 2122600 Fax + 31 (0)30 2512097 CBS-KNAW Fungal Biodiversity Centre 2014 
